$argv and $argc are global variables when php-cli is invoked, but the linter doesn't know about these 2 magic variables. 
as a workaround, cli scripts can currently do
```php
#!/usr/bin/env php
<?php
/** @var int $argc */
/** @var string[] $argv */
var_dump($argc, $argv);
```
and the linter won't complain, but would be nice if the linter had built-in support for these variables.

